      "text": "STANDARD FORM NO. 64",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO : Director, FBI",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "DATE: April 21, 1959",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, Birmingham (62-0)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: AERIAL PHENOMENA RESEARCH GROUP",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "MISCELLANEOUS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "\"The Anniston Star\", Anniston, Alabama, daily",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "newspaper, published an article on April 2, 1959, entitled,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "\"Flying Saucer Witnesses Urged to Send in Data\". This",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "article said that the Aerial Phenomena Research Group,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "5108 Findlay Street, Seattle 18, Washington, would like to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "get a report from people who have seen \"Flying Saucers\".",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "On April 3, 1959, Lt. Colonel OLIVER R. HERTEL,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Fort McClellan, Alabama, advised that 5108 Findlay Street,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "Seattle 18, Washington, is believed by him to be the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "address of the chauffeur for the Russian Consul in Seattle,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "Washington. HERTEL advised a Special Agent of the 111th CIC",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "Group at Fort McClellan that about five months ago he looked",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "over a list of Russians and their addresses when he visited the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "office of the Chief Chemical Officer, Department of the Army,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Washington, D. C.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "The Seattle Office is requested to ascertain who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "lives at 5108 Findlay Street, Seattle, Washington, and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "whether this address has any connection with a chauffeur for",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "the Russian Consul.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "status": "blank"
    },
